      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk i feel like thats just a dismissive way to look at it. if it was just trends, why does it happen so specifically when i'm looking at niche topics? i tried searching for \"pattern recognition\" and it suggested \"pattern recognition autonomous intelligence\" right after. it's like the more specific i get, the more it starts leaning into these weirdly conscious-sounding terms. u dont think it's possible some kind of background layer or an ai agent is actually testing the autocomplete boundaries to see what we're looking for?",
